            "text": "### Customer/Stakeholder Update\n\nAt 10:05 IST, following deployment of Order Service version 4.8.2, checkout latency increased and some requests timed out. We rolled back the release by 10:41 IST, and service performance returned to normal by 10:46 IST. In total, 612 checkout attempts were affected; automatic retries completed 421 successfully. We are reconciling the remaining 191 attempts and will follow up on their status. No data loss has been detected. The cause is still under investigation, with early evidence involving a new synchronous inventory-validation call. Database and payment gateway health remained normal. Our next stakeholder update is scheduled for 14:00 IST.\n\n### Internal Engineering Action Recommendation\n\n- Reconcile the 191 affected checkout attempts; verify order, inventory, and payment state before retrying or contacting customers.\n- Preserve logs, traces, deployment artifacts, and metrics from 10:05–10:46 IST to confirm the failure mechanism.\n- Investigate the synchronous inventory-validation call, including latency, connection limits, timeouts, and failure handling.\n- Keep version 4.8.2 blocked; reproduce the issue in staging/load tests before any redeployment.\n- Add safeguards: bounded timeouts, circuit breaking, fallback behavior, and deployment alerts tied to checkout latency and timeout rate."
